1.		Overview
The objective of this document is to provide a comprehensive guide on the architecture and inner workings behind the implementation of “The Tale of Tux”. “The Tale of Tux” is a web-based text game and makes a perfect project for beginner developers looking to build their first web-application

*****
(Note: formatting is messy, but will furnish, such as tabs and spaces. will fix when tech spec is looking near complete)
*****

2.		Summary


2.1		Background Story
<<Name of the Location>> is an imaginary world full of exciting adventures waiting for the ones who seek excitement. The goal of the game (selected by the user) is protected by the evil but mysterious cuboid monster, The Brick. Unfortunately to get to him Player must pass series of tasks and quests to be allowed to reach him. Maybe that is for good, as during those adventures Player will gain certain skills and artifacts which can help them to in the final combat. 


2.2		Overview of Game
“The Tale of Tux” is a role-playing game which takes place in a imaginary world filled with excitement and evil monsters. Users will be able to create custom characters and go on quests in order to defeat the evil but mysterious cuboid monster, The Brick.


3.		Game Play Look and Feel


3.1		Appearance


3.1.1		Welcome page with Character selection
On the entry page in the beginning of a game Player will select their Character from available list. Options are as follows:
a) Viking
b) Warrior Princess
c) Cheese
d) Pine Cone
e) Horny Mushroom

After select the character, Player will choose their main goal. Options are as follows:
a) Save Prince
b) Milk Cow
c) Plant Tree
d) Eat the most delicious ice-cream in the world before it melts

The last option to select will be starting character’s attributes. Those include:
a) Strength (offensive)
b) Health (defensive)
c) Intelligence (giving more options in some events)

User is given the total of 100 points to redistribute among all parameters. None of the parameters can be set to less than 10 points. 

After all points are redistributed Player will be able to go further to the next step.


3.1.2		First quest – Event T
User is located IN FRONT of CITY GATES and will have to finish the first small quest which is linked with tutorial. Features will be shown on the page: 
a) Character page: attributes 
b) Backpack content and usage: removing items adding items, browsing through them (displaying attributes add-ons)
c) Options 
d) Go to City
e) Hints Page: each event or location will have a small note attached to it with a hint how to progress. 


3.1.3		City – the main hub
Center location from where User has an option to go to selected locations:
a) Mountains // visible if (mountain penguin = 0); 
b) Forest // visible if (forest penguin = 0);
c) Desert // visible if (desert penguin = 0);
d) Python’s Nest

3.1.4	 	Forest
Player will go through series of events in this location. 
In the 1.0 version Player will go through all Forest events and only after finishing it will be able to go to other location. 

NICE TO HAVE: After finishing each event Player will be able to choose if they want to go to the next event or want to return to the City. In case Player returns to the city system will remember which was the last finished event in the location which was left. After coming back to the Forest again system will open the first not started event 


3.1.4.1 	Event Goat Adventure
<p> You are crossing the meadow where group of goats are walking around. What do you do? </p>

<button 1> Chase one of the goats and kill it. </button>
<button 2> Walk away </button>
<button 3> Pick some flowers and gets some rest </button>

Switch (button):
    Case (button 1):
        <p> You have killed the goat, but all that running made you hungry. You set up the fire and roast the goat. (+30 Health) </p>

        health += 30;

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 2):
        <p> When exiting the meadow you have found a goat-keeper sleeping in the bushes. You wake him up. 
        "Hey there. You should watch out for your goats, because some animal might attach them. There are plenty of wild beasts in this forest, you know."
        Goat-keeper thanks you for the warning and gives you some goat milk to drink. +5 Health </p>

        health += 5;
	metGoatKeeper = true; // this boolean is important for the next event

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 3):
        <p> You are hanging out on the meadow, watching goats when a grumpy goat-keeper comes to you
        GK: "What are you doing around my goats?"
        You: "Just hanging out and getting some rest. Is there something wrong?"
        GK: "I already lost few goats this month, killed by some tramps like you. Go away or I’ll punch you."
        What do you do? </p>

	metGoatKeeper = true; // this boolean is important for the next event

        <button 1.1> Fight </button>
        <button 1.2> Walk away </button>

        Switch (button):
            Case (button 1.1):
                <p> You attack the goat-keeper (Strength 100) </p>

	        fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength)
	        fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 100)

	        <p> Your attack: <<fightYout>>. Goat-keeper's attack <<fightOpponent >> </p>

	        if (fightYou >= fight Opponent):
	            <p> You have beaten up the goat keeper and took his money and food (+50$, +10 Health) </p>

	            health += 10;
	            money +=50;

<<NEXT EVENT>>

	        else:
	            <p> Goat keeper kicked your ass and left the meadow. (-20 Health).
	            Feeling ashamed to be beaten up by a goat-keeper you are walking away promising yourself never to tell anyone about what has happened here. </p>

	            health -= 20;

	            if (health <= 0):
	                <popup message> You have died. Game Lost</popup message>
<END OF GAME>



            Case (button 1.2):
                <p> Goat keeper curse you but you don't case and simply walk away. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>


3.1.4.2 	Merchant
<p> You are walking on the road and meeting a merchant with goods. What do you do? </p>

<button 1> Ignore him and move on</button>
<button 2> Attack and try to take his goods</button>
<button 3> Try to buy something</button>
if intelligence > 40
    <button 4> Start conversation </button>

Switch (button):
    Case (button 1):
        <p> Merchant is trying to sell you something, but you reply him "I am in the rush to <<insert game goal>> and cannot talk with you now. Maybe next time. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 2):
        <p> Merchant is fighting back. Strength 50. You say: "My name is Inigo Montoya. You killed my father. Prepare to die". </p>

        fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength);
        fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 50);

        <p> Your attack: <<fightYou>>. Merchant's attack <<fightOpponent>> </p>

        if (fightYou < fightOpponent):
            Health -= 15;

            if (health <= 0):
                <popup message> You have died. Game Lost</popup message>

<END OF GAME>

            else: // you lose the fight but you are still alive
                <p> You have lost the fight (-15 Health) but merchant lets your go. He feels pity for an orphan and gives you a bottle of whisky (+5 health, -10 intelligence) 
                Do you want to put it in your backpack or leave it. </p>

                <button 2.1> Yes </button>
                <button 2.2> No </button>

		Switch (button):
		    Case (button 2.1): // yes, take it
                
                      if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                        add.backpack(whisky)
			Health += 5;
	                Intelligence -= 10;

<<NEXT EVENT>>

                      else  // not space in backpack, all slots are filled
                        <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

                    Case (button 2.1):
                      <popup> You didn't take the whisky </popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

        else: // if you win fight
            <p> You have won the fight (Strength +5), but you leave the merchant go after taking his goods: money 80, knife (+5 Strength), sword (+20 Strength), whisky (+5Health, -10 Intelligence) </p>

            Money += 80;
            Strength += 5; // gained at the fight
            

            <p> Do you want to put a knife in your backpack? </p>

            <button 2.1.1> Yes</button>
            <button 2.1.2> No</button>

            if (button 2.1.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize):
                    add.backpack(knife)
                    strength += 5;



                else:  // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 2.1.2): // don't take it
                <popup> You didn't take the knife </popup>
			 
            <p> Do you want to put a sword in yout backpack? </p>

            <button 2.2.1> Yes </button>
            <button 2.2.2> No </button>

            if (button 2.2.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                    add.backpack(sword)
                    strength += 20;

                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 2.2.2)
                <popup> You didn't take the sword </popup>

            <p> Do you want to put whisky in your backpack?</p>

            <button 5.1> Yes</button>
            <button 5.2> No</button>

            if (button 5.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                    add.backpack(whisky)
                    health += 5;
		    intelligence -= 10;


                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 5.2):
                <popup> You didn't take the whisky</popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 3):  // buy something
	<p> Merchant shows you his goods:</p>

	<checkbox 1.1> sword (+20 Strength), price 500$ </checkbox>
	<checkbox 1.2> whisky (+5Health, -10 Intelligence). price 50$ </checkbox 1.2>
	if (intelligence > 30):
	    <checkbox 1.3>knife (+5 Strength), price 200$ </checkbox>
	<checkbox 1.4> No thanks, I don't need anything. </checkbox>
	<button 3.1> Submit </button>

	if (checkbox 1.4 == false)

	    // sword purchase
	    if (checkbox 1.1 == true) 

	        if (money >= 500)
	            money -= 500;

	       		if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(sword)
              		      strength+= 20;
			  

                	    else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money +=500;
			     
		else // if money <500
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy a sword.</p>

	    //whisky purchase
	    if (checkbox 1.2 == true) 

	        if (money >= 50)
	            money-=50;

            		  if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(whisky)
              		      health += 5;
		   	      intelligence -= 10;
			  

                	  else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money +=50;
	
		     
		else // if money <50
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy whisky.</p>

	    // knife purchase
	    if (checkbox 3.3 == true) 

	        if (money >= 200)
	            money-=200;

            		    if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(knife)
              		      strength += 5;
			  
                	    else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money+=200;
		     
		else // if money <200
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy a knife.</p>	            
	   
<<NEXT EVENT>>

	else // if checkbox don’t want to buy anything is on
	    <p> You reply: "Hmm. Maybe next time. I don't see anything interesting."</p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

	Case (button 4): //start conversation
		<p>You start conversation with the merchant, but after he realizes that you are not interested in his goods, he walks away. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>


3.1.4.3 	Hole
<p> You want to enter the forest. The forest is dark. It's night. You need some kind of light to show you the way. </p>

if (metGoatKeeper == true) 
	<button 1> Go back to the meadow and ask the goat-keeper for some candle or a flashlight. </button>

// THIS CAN BE VISIBLE ONLY IF IN THE FOREST EVENT 1- GOATS YOU HAVE MET A GOATKEEPER - IN THE FIRST SELECTION OPTION 2 OR 3 WERE CHOOSEN>>

<button 2> Go in without any light. </button>
<button 3> Camp the night and wait for the morning. </button>
   

Switch (button):

	case (button 1): // go back
	    <p> You went back to the goat-keeper for some kind of candle. but the goat-keeper disappeared. All you see in the meadow is coals from the goat-keeper fire. You pick up a branch and light it up with a coal. Now you can enter the forest. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

	case (button 2): // go in dark
   	    <p> You enter the forest without any light. You cannot see anything, its all dark around you. You make a few steps and you fall into a deep hole in the ground.

    	    <button 2.1> Try to climb out with your hands. </button>
            <button 2.2> Start crying. </button>
    	    <button 2.3> You make a rope out of your cloth. </button>


    	    switch (button)

		case (button 2.1): 
			<p> You try to climb up… You start climbing and in the middle of the hole you fall back and brake your back. Nobody know you are stuck there so after a few days you die of starvation. </p>

<END OF GAME>
		case (button 2.2):
			<p> you start crying!! thinking that you will never leave this hole again. Someone heard your crying, you hear foot steps above you. Someone throw a rope to you, and you are climbing out When you get out there is nobody there!!!!

<<NEXT EVENT>>

		case (button 2.3):    
			<p> You make a rope out of your clothes. You made a rope out of your clothes. You are more intelligent than you gave your self credit (+10 intelligence). You got out of the hole.

			intellegence += 10;

	case (button 3): // camp
		<p> You camp through the night outside the forest. At night a robber comes and takes 50% of your money. </p>

    		money *= 0.5;

        <p> You decide to: </p>

        <button 3.1> Fight him </button>
        <button 3.2> Pretend your still asleep.</button>

	switch (button)
   		case (button 3.1):
			<p> You want to fight him but he runs away leaving behind him every thing he took from you and he also drops a small ax (+35 strength). </p>

			money *=2 ;


		<p> Do you wish to pick up the small ax? </p>

     	        <button 3.4> Yes </button>
  		<button 3.5> No </button>
	
		switch (button):
			case (button 3.4): //yes, take it


	                  if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
        	            add.backpack(ax)
                	    strength+= 35;

	                  else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
        	            <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
	
        	  	case (button 3.5)
                	    <popup> You didn't take the ax</popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

		case (button 3.2) // You pretend your still asleep.
	 		<p> You pretend to sleep and actually did fall asleep. You proceed to wake up the next morning and regret not fighting back. Time to enter the forest...</p>


<<NEXT EVENT>>


3.1.4.4 	River
<p> You reached a crossroad in an enchanted forest. You can:

<button 1> Go left to shortcut in the dark part of the forest. </button>
<button 2> Go through the long and safe way of the forest. </button>

switch (button):
	case (button 1):
	    <p> You reached a one eye demon, if you want to pass this way you have to fight. Roll the dice to see if you can bit him (demon roll dice too). </p>

		fightYou = Math.random() * 6 + 1;
		fightOpponent = Math.random() * 6 + 1;

		do:
		  if (fightYou >= fightOpponent)
    		    <p> You win! you can keep going through the path. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

		  else (demonRoll > fightOpponent)
		    <p> the demon wins! you lose (-10 health). To keep going you have to pay him 10$ (-10$) </p>
		    health -= 10;

      		    if (health < 0)
		      <p> You died. End of the game </p>
<END OF GAME>
    
    		    if (money < 10)
		      <p> You don't have enough money to go through. Play again to try to pass </p>
		    else:
			<p> You have paid 10$ to pass through.</p>
			money -=10;
<<NEXT EVENT>>
		
		while (fightYou < fightOpponent)

	


	case (button 2):
	    <p> The player keep walking and he reached a river which he have to cross. </p>

	    if (backpack contains knife or ax):
	      <button 2.1> You can build a raft if you have an ax/knife. </button>
	    <button 2.2> Try to swim across </button>
	    <button 2.3> Pay the river keeper 15$ to get him across safely. </button>

	    switch (button):
		case (button 2.1):
			<p> You user your ax/knife to build a raft. you reached the other side of the river but your tired. You lose 5 point of strength. </p>

		        strength -= 5;

		case (button 2.2):
			<p> You try to swim across and you didn’t made it...
			You lose 5 point of strength, And you are back on the same (-5 strength)
			side of the river with the option to: </p>
			
			<button 2.2.2> Pay the river keeper 15$ to get him across safely. </button>
			
		case (button 2.3 or button 2.2.2):		
			if (money >= 15)
				<p> You payed 15$ to the river keeper. The river keeper got you across safely but demanded from you extra $25. </p>	
				if (money >=40)
					<p> You payed 40$ to the river keeper cursing him heavily. </p>	
					money -= 40;

				else // don't have 40
					<p> You gave all your money you had left to the river keeper cursing him heavily. </p>	
					money =0;

			else // if don't have 15 money.
 				<p> You gave whatever money you had to the river keeper and he took you to the other side of the river. </p>	
					money = 0;
    	
<<NEXT EVENT>>




3.1.4.5 	Dead Body
<p> You are walking through the forest and you have tripped over something. When you look at it you can see human body covered with blood. What do you do? </p>	
				
<button 1> You are running away in case there is an attacker in the area </button>
<button 2> You examine the body and the surroundings </button>

switch (button):
	case (button 1):
		<p>You have run away in panic and lost some money you had still left in your pockets</p>
		money = 0;

	case (button 2):
		<p>While examining the body you have found some money (+30$) and following artefacts:axe (+30 strength),book “The Mythical Man Month” (15 Intelligence), book “Biography of Grace Hopper” ( 10 Intelligence),  apple (+5 Health). You have read all the books, but now you have to decide what to do with remaining items. </p>
		money += 30;
		intelligence += 25;

		<p> Do you want to put ax in your backpack?</p>

	            <button 2.1> Yes</button>
        	    <button 2.2> No</button>

            	    if (button 2.1) // yes, take it

	                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
        	            add.backpack(ax)
	                    health += 30;


	                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
        	            <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>

	            if (button 2.2)
        	        <popup> You didn't take the sword </popup>


		<p> Do you want to put apple in your backpack?</p>

	            <button 2.3> Yes</button>
        	    <button 2.4> No</button>

            	    if (button 2.3) // yes, take it

	                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
        	            add.backpack(apple)
	                    health += 5;


	                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
        	            <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>

	            if (button 2.4)
        	        <popup> You didn't take the apple</popup>


<<NEXT EVENT>>

