3.1.5		Desert
Player will go through series of events in this location. 
In the 1.0 version Player will go through all Desert events and only after finishing it will be able to go to other location. 

NICE TO HAVE (not in this phase): After finishing each event Player will be able to choose if they want to go to the next event or want to return to the City. In case Player returns to the city system will remember which was the last finished event in the location which was left. After coming back to the Forest again system will open the first not started event 

# some notes:
# What will the items in merchant story do?
# logic to story 1: simplified and given some other logic.


3.1.5.1 	Dessert Desert
<p>The world beginnings to blur. The sand below begins to stick the bottom of your feet. </p>

<button 1> Continue walking. </button>
if (intelligence > 12) // then option 2 is visible
    <button 2> Investigate. </button>

switch (button):
	case (button 1) // walk 1
    		<p> You continue walking. Your feet are growing heavy. </p>

    		<button 1.1> Continue walking.. </button>
  		  if (intelligence > 12) # then option 2 is visible
        	    <button 1.2> Investigate. </button>
		  
		  switch (button):
			case (button 1.1): //walk2
				<p>You continue walking. Your feet are growing heavy. You look down and see what's wrong: You're sinking and you are already in the sand till your knees</p>
			
				<button 1.1.1>Make like a rock and roll.</button>	
				<button 1.1.2>Freak out!</button>
				
				switch (button):
					case (button 1.1.1): //rock and roll
						<p>You do a barrel roll, again and again until you're out of the quicksand.</p>				

					case (button 1.1.2): // freakout
						<p>You freak out hardcore, and continue to sink. Unfortunately the more you struggle the more you sink it. Now you realize that staying cool and rolling off would be wiser, but it's too late. You die. GAME OVER</p>	

<END OF GAME>
	
			case (button 1.2): // investigate2
				<p>You investigate the area and see that you are ankles deep in the sand. That is something not right. You return back by your steps without any sudden move. You have realized that was the beginning of quicksand. You would be in great trouble if you didn't notice that on time. Find a way around this dangerous area and circle around the quicksand. </p>
	
<<NEXT EVENT>>
	
	case (button 2): // investigate1
    		<p> You get down on one knee for a closer look at the sand. It smells sugary. You lean in closer to smell the sand. Definitely sugar. </p>

    		<button 2.1> Continue walking.. </button>
        	<button 2.2> Lick the sand. </button>

		switch (button):
			case (button 2.1): //walk3
				<p>You have decided that you are loosing your mind and have to leave as soon as possible from this horrible place. You continue walking until weird sensation is gone. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

			case (button 2.2): //lick
				<p>It's super weird but you lick the sand. It tastes like sugar. It's definitely sugar. Yum. Your health is increasing (+5 Health) </p>
				health +=5;

<<NEXT EVENT>>





<<NEXT EVENT>>


3.1.5.2 	Merchant


<p> You are walking through the desert when somewhere on the horisont you see a figure approaching you. You recognize that he's a merchant with goods. What do you do? </p>

<button 1> Ignore him and move on</button>
<button 2> Attack and try to take his goods</button>
<button 3> Try to buy something</button>
if intelligence > 30
    <button 4> Start conversation </button>

Switch (button):
    Case (button 1):
        <p> Merchant is trying to sell you something, but you reply him "Naaaah. I'm good." and you walk away.</p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 2):
        <p> Merchant is fighting back. Strength 30. You say: "Hasta la vista baby!" </p>

        fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength);
        fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 30);

        <p> Your attack: <<fightYou>>. Merchant's attack <<fightOpponent>> </p>

        if (fightYou < fightOpponent):
            Health -= 20;

            if (health <= 0):
                <popup message> You have died. Game Lost</popup message>

<END OF GAME>

            else: // you lose the fight but you are still alive
