        			fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength);
			        fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 150);

			        <p> Your attack: <<fightYou>>. Dragon's attack <<fightOpponent>> </p>

		        	if (fightYou < fightOpponent):
	        			Health -= 50;

					if (health <= 0):
                				<popup message> You have died. Game Lost</popup message>		
<END OF GAME>

				       	else: // you lost the fight but you are still alive
        				       <p> You have lost the fight (-50 Health), but you are still alive. You run away from the dragon and stupid fairy who got you into this. After you are far far away you only stop to get some rest and promise yourself never to fight a dragon for any fairy. NEVER.</p>	

				else: // if you win fight
           				<p> You have won the fight (Strength +50) and fairy gives you take the super sword (+60 Strength).
					Do you want to put it in your backpack ?</p>
			
             				<button 2.1> Yes </button>	
					<button 2.2> No </button>
				
					strength += 50; // from the fight

					Switch (button):
			  		  Case (button 2.1): // yes, take it
                	
                		          if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                        			add.backpack(superSword)
						Strength += 60
<<NEXT EVENT>>

		                          else  // not space in backpack, all slots are filled
			                        <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>




			case (button 3.2): // don't attach dragon
				<p> You think "This fairy must be crazy if she thinks I will go for that." You reject fairy's offer and go back on your quest for search for mountain penguin</p>
<<NEXT EVENT>>

	
3.1.6.3		Merchant in Mountains

<p> You are walking on the road up the mountain when you see a merchant with goods. What do you do? </p>

<button 1> Ignore him and move on</button>
<button 2> Attack and try to take his goods</button>
<button 3> Try to buy something</button>
if intelligence > 40
    <button 4> Start conversation </button>

Switch (button):
    Case (button 1):
        <p> Merchant is trying to sell you something, but you reply him "If you don't have any penguins I'm afraid I don't need anything else". You walk away.</p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 2):
        <p> Merchant is fighting back. Strength 70. You say: "Fear me, if you dare". </p>

        fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength);
        fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 70);

        <p> Your attack: <<fightYou>>. Merchant's attack <<fightOpponent>> </p>

        if (fightYou < fightOpponent):
            Health -= 25;

            if (health <= 0):
                <popup message> You have died. Game Lost</popup message>

<END OF GAME>

            else: // you lose the fight but you are still alive
                <p> You have lost the fight (-25 Health) but merchant lets your go. He feels pity for an orphan and gives you a bottle of whisky (+5 health, -10 intelligence) 
                Do you want to put it in your backpack or leave it. </p>

                <button 2.1> Yes </button>
                <button 2.2> No </button>

		Switch (button):
		    Case (button 2.1): // yes, take it
                
                      if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                        add.backpack(whisky)
			Health += 5;
	                Intelligence -= 10;

<<NEXT EVENT>>

                      else  // not space in backpack, all slots are filled
                        <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

                    Case (button 2.1):
                      <popup> You didn't take the whisky </popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

        else: // if you win fight
            <p> You have won the fight (Strength +5), but you leave the merchant go after taking his goods: money 80, small knife (+5 Strength), large sword (+25 Strength), whisky (+5Health, -10 Intelligence) </p>

            Money += 80;
            Strength += 5; // gained at the fight
            

            <p> Do you want to put a small knife in your backpack? </p>

            <button 2.1.1> Yes</button>
            <button 2.1.2> No</button>

            if (button 2.1.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize):
                    add.backpack(smallKnife)
                    strength += 5;



                else:  // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 2.1.2): // don't take it
                <popup> You didn't take the small knife </popup>
			 
            <p> Do you want to put a large sword in yout backpack? </p>

            <button 2.2.1> Yes </button>
            <button 2.2.2> No </button>

            if (button 2.2.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                    add.backpack(largeSword)
                    strength += 20;

                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 2.2.2)
                <popup> You didn't take the sword </popup>

            <p> Do you want to put whisky in your backpack?</p>

            <button 5.1> Yes</button>
            <button 5.2> No</button>

            if (button 5.1) // yes, take it

                if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
                    add.backpack(whisky)
                    health += 5;
		    intelligence -= 10;


                else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                    <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>


            if (button 5.2):
                <popup> You didn't take the whisky</popup>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

    Case (button 3):  // buy something
	<p> Merchant shows you his goods:</p>

	<checkbox 1.1> large sword (+25 Strength), price 450$ </checkbox>

	<checkbox 1.2> whisky (+5Health, -10 Intelligence). price 50$ </checkbox>

	if (intelligence > 30):
	    <checkbox 1.3>small knife (+5 Strength), price 100$ </checkbox>

	<checkbox 1.4> No thanks, I don't need anything. </checkbox>


	<button 3.1> Submit </button>

	if (checkbox 1.4 == false)

	    // sword purchase
	    if (checkbox 1.1 == true) 

	        if (money >= 450)
	            money -= 450;

	       		if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(largeSword)
              		      strength+= 25;
			  

                	    else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money +=450;
			     
		else // if money <450
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy a sword.</p>

	    //whisky purchase
	    if (checkbox 1.2 == true) 

	        if (money >= 50)
	            money-=50;

            		  if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(whisky)
              		      health += 5;
		   	      intelligence -= 10;
			  

                	  else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money +=50;
	
		     
		else // if money <50
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy whisky.</p>

	    // small knife purchase
	    if (checkbox 3.3 == true) 

	        if (money >= 100)
	            money-=100;

            		    if (backpack.length < backpackSize)
               		      add.backpack(smallKnife)
              		      strength += 5;
			  
                	    else // we do not have space, all slots are filled
                                <popup> Sorry, your backpack is full. You cannot add anything more to your backpack <popup>
				money+=100;
		     
		else // if money <100
		    <p> You don’t have enough money to buy a knife.</p>	            
	   
<<NEXT EVENT>>

	else // if checkbox don’t want to buy anything is on
	    <p> You reply: "No thanks, I don't need anything"</p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>

	Case (button 4): //start conversation
		<p>You start conversation with the merchant, but after he realizes that you are not interested in his goods, he walks away. </p>

<<NEXT EVENT>>


