mountainPenguin += true;
penguinCount ++;

<button1>RETURN TO CITY </button>
<<RETURN TO CITY>>




3.1.7		Python’s Nest
<<Python is protecting the entrance to the Brick Hub. In order to get pass through Python 3 penguins has to be collected (one from each Location). 
If a Player goes to the Python with less than 3 penguins Python will not let them through >>

if (penguinCount <3):
	<p>“I want you to bring me 3 penguins. Each of them is in different location in somewhere in the area. Only then I will let you through.” </p>

Once Player collects all penguins and will come to the Python’s Nest option appears:

if (penguinCount = 3)
	<p> Python says: “I can see you have brought me penguins. Let me take care of them from now on." What do you do? </p>
	
	<button 1> Do not give penguins to the python  </button>
	<button 2> Give penguins to the python </button>

	if (button 1):
		<p> You didn't give penguins to the Pythons and tried to protectem. Python ate you instead of penguins. You died. Game OVER.</p>

<END OF GAME>

	if (button 1):
		<p> Python ate penguins, but lets you through.</p>
		<button 1.1> Go to Mysterious Hut</button>

<<NEXT EVENT : Bricks Hut>>


3.1.8		Brick’s Hut
<<The final battle with the Brick monster. Brick.strength = 200, Player.strength = from character attributes.>>


<p>You have found what you have been looking for all the way. The only thing that prevents you from fulfilling your mission is the mysterious monster hiding in his hut. You can finally fight him to <<gameGoal>>. The monster is a Brick </p> 

do: 	
	roundNo = 1
	finalBattleScore = 0

	<p> Round <<roundNo>>  </p> 
	<button 1.1> Fight</button>
	
	roundNo ++;
	fightYou = Math.floor (Math.random() * Strength);
	fightOpponent = Math.floor (Math.random() * 200);

        <p> Your attack: <<fightYou>>. Brick's attack <<fightOpponent>> </p>
		

        if (fightYou < fightOpponent): // you loose round
	<p> You lost the round <<roundNo>. </p>          

        else: // you won round
	<p> You won the round <<roundNo>></p>
	finalBattleScore ++;

	
while (round <6)

if (finalBattleScore <3)
	<p> You were too weak to fight off the Brick. You lost the game. GAME OVER

<END OF GAME>

else:	
	<p> Congrats!! You won the fight with the Brick and you have managed to <<gameGoal>>. Well Done!!! The End.</p>

<END OF GAME>



a) 5 rounds of battle,
b) Player has to win at least 3 rounds.
c) Strength of player and Brick defined by random number between 0 and their strength parameters. 
If Player wins the round message: “You have won this round, but Brick is attacking you again”
If Player wins the round message: “You have lost this round and Brick laughs at you”

If Player wins at least 3 rounds message:” Congrats!!! You have won the fight and Brick is defeated. You are laughing and dancing over its dead corpse. 
You have managed to <<goal_name>> and Brick could not stop you!”
If Player loses at least 3 rounds message: “Buhu, you have lost with Brick and he kills you. Maybe you will try in other life. GAME LOST!!!”

End of the Game


3.1.9		Penguins
Penguins are small creatures wandering around at the end of every locations path. Once Player finishes all the events in one location one penguin will join and will follow from now on. No backpack pocket is needed for a penguins’ collection. Info of penguins collected should be visible on the tool bar. 
There will be 4 variables created for recording penguins collection. Three boolean for each locations' penguin marking that this penguin from that particular location has been collected and one integer variable for penguin count where counting of penguins will be recorded. 
Boolean variables will be used to mark down if the location should be disabled (in case all events from that location were finished and penguin was found).
Integer variable will be used to check in Pythons' nest if player has collected all three penguins.


